         <h1 id="post-58">Information for Authors</h1>
<div id="print_icon">
</div>

<!-- <br clear="all" /> -->
<hr class="h2" />
          <div class="storycontent">
            <h3>Conference Speaker Requirements</h3>
<p>The presentation should be delivered to the session moderator on an USB stick at the latest 5-10 minutes before the session starts. The <strong>presentation format </strong>can be Powerpoint (.ppt – office version 2003/2007), an open document presentation (.odp) or a pdf file. <strong>Recommended font size is 24 point or larger</strong> for presentations, as some of your audience will be a good distance from the screen.</p>
<p>Please notice that the <strong>presentations will be run on a PC and projector supplied by the conference organisers</strong>. Your presentation will be pre-loaded on the PC and ready to project at the time of you presentation. You may NOT use your own PC! This disrupts the flow of the conference.</p>
<p>The PCs used will have internet access so if you need to demonstrate something on the web there should be no problem. </p>
<p>Speakers can feel free to contact their session moderator or Mr. Niels Fromm (mail: fromm@cms.hu-berlin.de) if they have any questions about presenting at the conference. <br/><br/></p>
          </div>
